ave shaped environmental issues. Fiorino grounds his discussion with references to numerous specific cases, including radon, global warming, lead, and hazardous wastes. Timely and necessary, this is an invaluable handbook for students, activists, and anyone wanting to unravel contemporary American environmental politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmental policyxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aEnvironmental policyzUnited StateszUnited States. 0aEnvironmental policyzUnited States. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520915466?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520915466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520915466/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles